Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
init_import_mode(25.10)                                init_import_mode(25.10)

Name
       init_import_mode

Syntax
         init_import_mode <import_mode_parameters>

       Type: String

       Default: NULL

       You  can  use this global variable to set the options of the setImport-
       Mode command (import mode parameters). The string with the  options  of
       the  setImportMode  command can be passed during the design initializa-
       tion. This  global  variable  replaces  the  previous  rda_Input(ui_im-
       port_mode) configuration file variable.

Example
       The following command passes the -discardFloatingVNets true -keepEmpty-
       Module true options of the setImportMode command during initialization:

       set init_import_mode {-discardFloatingVNets true -keepEmptyModule true}

       Note:

              * Empty  modules  and  cells  without  physical cell definitions
                should not be converted into blackboxes and partitions.

              * Empty modules should be retained.

Related Information
